The president is delivering the annual State of the Nation Address before Parliament. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa is delivering the annual State of the Nation Address (Sona) before Parliament. Sona is a joint sitting of the two Houses of Parliament and provides the president with an opportunity to speak to the nation on the general state of South Africa, to reflect on a wide range of political, economic and social matters within the domestic and global contexts, to account to the nation on the work of government and to set out governmentâ€™s programme of action. WATCH: Sona 2019 